text: In nomine Domini.Denewulf bisceop & þa hiwan in Wintanceastre leton to Beornulfa hiora landesXVhida æt Eblesburnan wið þam gafole ðe he wið bisceop & wið hiwan ared.

Ðæt isXLVscilling to hærfestes emnihte sie <simle> <agyfen> on ða gerad ðæt hine nage nan man of to aceapienne ne his bearn æfter his dege þa hwile þe hi ða gerihta forðbringan a magen & eac ælce geare fultumien to þære cyrican bote þe ðet land to <hyrð> be ðem dæle þe ðet oðer folc do, ælc be his landes meðe & þa cyricsceattes mid rihte agyfe, & <fyrde> & brycge & <festengeweorc> hewe swa mon ofer eall folc do.
& ðis wes gedon on ðara witena gewitnesse & <ðafunge> ðe hiora naman her benioðan <standað> awritene, ðe geare ðe wes agan fram Cristes acennesse twa winter & nigan hund.
& ðet wes gedon on þære mæran stowe on Wintanceastre.
Bisceop lyfde Beornulfe his mege þæt he moste þa inberðan menn hamettan to Eblesburnan.
Nu hebbe ic hi hamet, Lufe & hire ðreo bearn & Luhan & his seax bearn.
Ðonne geærendodon me ða hiwan on Wintanceastre ðet þa men mostan on þan londe wunien, hæfde swa ic swa minra freonda swelce hit hæfde.
Þonne weron þær ðreo witeðeowe men burbærde & ðreo ðeowberde.
Ða me salde bisceop & þa hiwan to ryhtre æhta & hire team.
Ðis wes gedon ða man þa cyricean halgode æt Hysseburnan, on ðara manna gewitnessa þe hira naman her beneoðan <standað>.
